<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./675: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-09T19:00:00-05:00">October 9, 1929—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>76. Do you consider that the present time is favorable for Pan
                                American Airways to apply for an operating concession in
                                Honduras?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>